[8.524292, "o", "cat /root/material_density_table.md\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[8.525107, "o", "# Proprietary Material Density Table\r\n\r\nThis table lists the density values for the proprietary materials used in the Constructo-95 system.\r\nUse the Material ID found in the CAD file attributes to lookup the corresponding density.\r\n\r\n| Material ID | Material Name | Density (g/cm³) | Description |\r\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\r\n| **1** | Generic Debris | 0.10 | Low-density dust/noise artifacts. |\r\n| **10** | Standard Steel | 7.85 | Common structural steel. |\r\n| **25** | Aluminum 6061 | 2.70 | Aerospace grade aluminum. |\r\n| **42** | Unobtanium | 5.55 | High-strength proprietary alloy. |\r\n| **99** | Lead | 11.34 | Heavy ballast material. |\r\n\r\n## Formula\r\n\r\n$$ Mass = Volume \\times Density $$\r\n\r\nNote: Ensure volume is in $cm^3$ and density is in $g/cm^3$.\r\n"]
[8.525348, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@8ac6954772f6:~# "]
